HEADWORD: Point switch
<hw>Point switch</hw>. <fld>(Railroads)</fld> <def>A switch made up of a rail from each track, both rails being tapered far back and connected to throw alongside the through rail of either track.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Poise</ent>⟦br⟧
